4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper also discusses anticipating and defending future actions of opponents in adversarial settings, which could involve cryptographic or security-related techniques.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper briefly mentions implementing the learning algorithms, which could involve systems and control techniques. However, this category is less likely than the others.
